task.summary: Default task
Major re-sync with danny's personal toolkit.
Very early stage topological graph stuff. Lots of cleanup here and there.
Changes to workspace.xml file as a result of using this project's src directories as content roots in other IntelliJ projects.
Implement a ValidatedJTextField class that makes it easier to manage the validation of JTextField values.
Resync time.
Lots of cleanup.
Preserve ExploreSSL as MyExploreSSL
Various cleanup. Update copyrights.
Commit and post an irrelevant change to ...MyExploreSSL. The real purpose of this is to make sure that I didn't screw anything up in my attempts to create a new project that referenced this project.
Cleanup copyright formatting. Possibly some other minor (probably textual cleanup) changes.
Make the TreeCounter class more flexible by changing the TreeCounter( TreeCounter<K> ) constructor to take a Counter<K> instead of a TreeCounter<K>.
First commit of the Pepys event handler. Lots of cleanup here and there.

Early check-in of packers modules (not ready for prime time). First commit and push of Pepys (event mechanism that uses Java's strong, weak and zombie references to assist in managing the lifecycle of event listeners). Minor cleanup elsewhere.
Snapshot time. Working mostly on the v2 unpacker. Still trying to get the distinction between instance ids and packing ids exactly right.
Packer2 family exhibits basic sanity.
Lots of cleanup.

Basic sanity for the Packer2 facility.
Supports packing and unpacking of all of the primitive Java types (byte, short, int, long, float, double and boolean) and their related container classes (Byte, Short, Integer, Long, Float, Double, Boolean and String), a collection class named Packable2Collection which can be used to pack and unpack arrays, sets, lists, etc, and a mapping class named Packable2Mapping which can be used to pack and unpack hashmaps and sorted maps and the like.
The software still needs a lot of cleanup. Significant API and file format changes are also still quite likely.

Rename the new packing facility as the Gowing packing facility.
Also a checkpoint commit before trying out idea of generating Gowing instance ids on an on-demand basis.

Cleaned up Gowing facility (better Javadocs, old commented out removed, etc). Marginal but useful cleanup on TreeSorter.java class. New first cut at generalizing the handling of messages (heading towards generalizing the logging window stuff).
Checkpoint commit prior to doing some experimenting on Niepce.
Checkpoint commit prior to doing some experimenting on Niepce.
Checkpoint commit and push prior to trip to Winnipeg.
Checkpoint commit prior to starting 2016 work.
Cleanup of the sorted JPanel facility (not really ready for primetime yet).

A sorted JPanel mechanism which keeps its components in sorted order.
Various enhancements to the TreeSorter class inspired by the needs of the sorted JPanel mechanism.
Reasonably robust sorted panels. Considerable cleanup, testing and even some bug fixing of ObtuseCalendarDate and ObtuseApproximateCalendarDate.
Reasonably robust sorted panels. Considerable cleanup, testing and even some bug fixing of ObtuseCalendarDate and ObtuseApproximateCalendarDate.
Reasonably robust sorted panels. Considerable cleanup, testing and even some bug fixing of ObtuseCalendarDate and ObtuseApproximateCalendarDate.
Experimenting with Java 8's Optional mechanism and incorporating into a few places (most notably, the Gowing facility).
Various cleanup and adding a few new methods to ObtuseUtil.

Implement auto-indenting of logging messages in com.util.Logger. Add a method to ObtuseUtil to detect if the running JVM is under the control of the Java debugger. Add a couple of methods to ObtuseUtil to do centering of text (much like lpad and rpad but they add spaces on both sides to 'center' the text). Clarify who is responsible for what in class-level Javadoc comment in the UniquelyNamedEntity class.
